description: From German Henotheismus, coined in the 19th century by German philosopher Friedrich Wilhelm Joseph von Schelling (1775–1854) from Ancient Greek ἕν (hén) (stem of εἷς (heîs, “one”)) + German Theismus (“theism”) (ultimately from Ancient Greek θεός (theós, “god”)).

entries.meaning: Belief in or worship of one deity without denying the existence of other deities.
